<paragraph blockId="36.[136,1451,806,1048]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,842,868]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1983" box="[294,529,842,868]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="priapus">
<emphasis box="[294,529,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Myoxanthus priapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kolanowska &amp; Szlachetko" authorityYear="2014" box="[697,852,843,868]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ortizianus">
<emphasis box="[697,852,843,868]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">M. ortizianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with which it shares the purple-yellowish flowers covered abaxially by short trichomes with the lateral sepals forming a suborbicular synsepal and petals yellowish purple stripped, obovate to oblong basally, then contracted and lip with a thick erect callus near the base. It can be distinguished by the basal half of the petals oblong to obovate then narrow 
<emphasis box="[988,1011,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">vs</emphasis>
. apex of the petals narrower forming a slender tail and an oblong lip with small acute lateral lobes near the middle 
<emphasis box="[974,997,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">vs</emphasis>
. lip weakly trilobed with rounded lateral lobes below the middle.
</paragraph>
